08/08/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Romanian Anti-Drug Agency appealed to local media on Thursday(7 August) to assist its efforts in fighting drug abuse. 
The agency urged journalists to join the initiative by popularising the National Strategy for the Fight Against Drugs. 
According to the agency, local media could assist by broadcasting educational and preventive messages, as well as regular reports on the government's latest anti-drug measures.The strategy should be implemented by the end of 2004. 
(Rompres - 07/08/03)
